Motorola Mobility Holdings Inc Sues Apple Inc. Over New iPhone-DJ
Wednesday, 25 Jan 2012 01:59pm EST
Dow Jones reported that Motorola Mobility Holdings Inc filed its latest patent infringement lawsuit against Apple Inc., targeting the recent version of the iPhone as Motorola's merger with Google Inc. moves toward final regulatory approval. Motorola filed suit in U.S. District Court for the Southern District of Florida, alleging Apple has infringed on six patents related to mobile technology.Â 
